    <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText><![CDATA[<pre>From the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [<a href='http://www.gpo.gov'>www.gpo.gov</a>]By Mr. AMASH:H.J. Res. 15.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:Article V of the Constitution empowers ``[t]he Congress,whenever two thirds of both Houses shall deem it necessary''to ``propose Amendments to this Constitution . . . which . .. shall be valid to all Intents and Purposes, as Part of thisConstitution, when ratified by the Legislatures of threefourths of the several States, or by Conventions in threefourths thereof.''[Page H98]</pre>]]></constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
